article.story: LITTLE ROCK, Ark. -- — KyKy Tandy's 25 points helped Jacksonville State defeat Little Rock 90-60 on Thursday night. Tandy shot 9 for 14 (3 for 4 from 3-point range) and 4 of 5 from the free throw line for the Gamecocks (6-7). Juwan Perdue added 14 points while going 6 of 11 from the field, and he also had seven rebounds. Quincy Clark shot 5 of 11 from the field and 3 for 4 from the line to finish with 13 points. Khalen Robinson led the Trojans (6-7) in scoring, finishing with 14 points, two steals and two blocks. Bradley Douglas added 12 points for Little Rock. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
